WEBVTT

00:59.601 --> 01:01.477
[HORSE NICKERS]

01:01.644 --> 01:03.145
REMEMBER WHAT
MR. NASH SAID TO ME

01:03.313 --> 01:06.106
WHEN I HAD TO SAY
GOOD-BYE TO MARY
AT THE BURTON SCHOOL?

01:09.569 --> 01:11.028
HE SAID,
"MAKE IT BRIEF.

01:13.114 --> 01:15.157
LONG GOOD-BYES
ARE ONLY PAINFUL."

01:28.713 --> 01:31.423
[NOISY HONKY-TONK
PIANO PLAYING]

01:35.095 --> 01:37.930
LORDY, MARY,
YOU'D NEVER BELIEVE
HOW BIG IT IS.

01:38.098 --> 01:39.181
IT SOUNDS BIG.

01:39.349 --> 01:40.974
WHAT'S ALL
THE MUSIC?

01:41.142 --> 01:42.476
IT'S COMING
FROM THE SALOON,

01:42.644 --> 01:45.187
JUST LIKE THE ONE
WE SAW ONCE
IN GOLD COUNTRY.

01:45.355 --> 01:47.606
PA'S NOT
GOING TO LIKE IT.

01:47.774 --> 01:49.149
Woman: WHY IS SHE
IN MY KITCHEN?

01:49.317 --> 01:52.194
YOU DON'T NEED
A KITCHEN TO MAKE
BISCUITS LIKE THESE.

01:52.362 --> 01:53.946
YOU NEED
A BLACKSMITH'S SHOP!

01:54.114 --> 01:55.239
Woman: I QUIT!

02:00.120 --> 02:02.079
THERE WILL BE NO MORE FOOD.
I JUST QUIT!

02:02.247 --> 02:03.205
Man:
HALLELUJAH!

02:03.373 --> 02:05.582
MRS. INGALLS,
GET THEM BISCUITS READY.

02:05.750 --> 02:07.668
FOLLOW ME.
I'LL TELL YOU ABOUT
THE REST OF YOUR DUTIES.

02:07.836 --> 02:09.419
Charles: GOOD LUCK.

02:13.258 --> 02:14.091
WHERE YOU GOING?

02:14.259 --> 02:15.259
WHAT BUSINESS
IS IT OF YOURS?

02:15.426 --> 02:16.635
WHY DON'T YOU JUST
GO OVER TO THE BAR

02:16.803 --> 02:17.886
AND GET YOURSELF
A DRINK?

02:18.054 --> 02:19.721
I DON'T WANT A DRINK.
I WANT SOME SLEEP.

02:19.889 --> 02:21.223
I DON'T WANT
ANY TROUBLE.

02:21.391 --> 02:23.851
WELL, THEN YOU GET
YOUR HAND OFF ME.

02:24.018 --> 02:25.227
Charles: CAROLINE?

02:25.395 --> 02:27.646
IN THE KITCHEN.
WHERE ELSE WOULD I BE?

02:27.814 --> 02:29.398
GOT CUSTOMERS
OUT HERE.

02:29.566 --> 02:31.400
OH, NOW, IF THEY THINK I'M
GOING TO SERVE

02:31.568 --> 02:32.526
MORE THAN 3 MEALS A DAY,

02:32.694 --> 02:34.236
THEY'VE GOT
ANOTHER THINK COMING.

02:34.404 --> 02:36.446
Alice:
TABLE FOR 3,
PLEASE, MISS.

02:36.614 --> 02:38.448
[LAUGHTER]

02:41.870 --> 02:43.579
DRIVER, THE BAGS!

02:45.498 --> 02:47.040
HEAVENS!

02:47.208 --> 02:48.625
FAST ENOUGH
FOR YOU, DEAR?

02:48.793 --> 02:51.712
OH, SHUT UP.
LET GO OF ME!

02:54.215 --> 02:56.341
STANDISH, HOW COME
YOU ALWAYS WIN?

02:56.509 --> 02:58.969
NEVER GAMBLE WITH
THE SON OF A GAMBLER.

02:59.137 --> 03:01.388
Albert: FIRE! FIRE!

03:01.556 --> 03:03.640
THE WINOKA SCHOOL
IS BURNING DOWN!

03:05.435 --> 03:06.977
HEY, COME ON.
LET'S WATCH IT!

03:17.238 --> 03:19.823
YOUNG MAN,
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

03:19.991 --> 03:23.285
UH, I'M WORKING
FOR THE CHURCH, MA'AM.

03:23.453 --> 03:25.579
GAMBLING'S A SIN.

03:25.747 --> 03:27.956
OH. YES, OF COURSE.

03:51.522 --> 03:54.524
WE KNOW THAT
LEONARDO DA VINCI
PAINTED "THE LAST SUPPER."

03:54.692 --> 03:58.237
NOW, WHO WERE
THE GUESTS OF JESUS?

03:58.404 --> 03:59.321
Girl:
PETER AND JOHN.

03:59.489 --> 04:00.989
RIGHT, SUE.

04:01.157 --> 04:02.658
10 MORE TO GO.

04:04.869 --> 04:06.245
Boy: THOMAS.

04:06.412 --> 04:07.621
RIGHT, THOMAS.

04:07.789 --> 04:09.873
I KNOW
THAT BECAUSE MY
NAME'S THOMAS.

04:10.041 --> 04:10.958
[CLASS LAUGHS]

04:11.125 --> 04:13.168
Mary: WHO ELSE?

04:13.336 --> 04:14.294
Second girl: SIMON.

04:14.462 --> 04:16.546
RIGHT. WHO ELSE?

04:18.800 --> 04:20.175
OH, MRS. INGALLS.

04:20.343 --> 04:22.552
MR. AMES, I'D LIKE
YOU TO MEET A VERY
DEAR FRIEND OF OURS

04:22.720 --> 04:24.221
FROM WALNUT GROVE--
ALICE GARVEY.

04:24.389 --> 04:25.305
HOW DO YOU DO?

04:25.473 --> 04:26.598
AND THIS IS
HER SON ANDY.

04:26.766 --> 04:27.891
IT'S
MY PLEASURE.

04:28.059 --> 04:29.268
WELL,
I'LL TELL MARY
YOU'RE HERE.

04:29.435 --> 04:32.020
NO. I REALLY DON'T
HAVE TIME TO VISIT.

04:32.188 --> 04:34.022
I JUST WANTED TO FIND
OUT WHERE THE SCHOOL IS.

04:34.190 --> 04:35.941
IT'S TIME WE GOT
THE CHILDREN ENROLLED.

04:36.109 --> 04:38.610
WELL, THERE
ISN'T A REGULAR
SCHOOL--

04:38.778 --> 04:40.404
JUST
A PRIVATE ONE.

04:40.571 --> 04:43.865
Caroline: IN A TOWN
THIS SIZE? WELL,
THAT'S HARD TO BELIEVE.

04:44.033 --> 04:45.742
HA HA! THE TOWN
COUNCIL IS MADE UP

04:45.910 --> 04:47.077
OF WEALTHY
CITIZENS.

04:47.245 --> 04:49.413
THEY SEND THEIR
CHILDREN TO THE
WINOKA SCHOOL.

04:49.580 --> 04:50.747
IT'S PRIVATE
AND, UH...

04:50.915 --> 04:52.541
EXPENSIVE.

04:52.709 --> 04:54.918
VERY.

04:55.086 --> 04:57.462
WELL, THAT SETTLES
THAT, DOESN'T IT?

04:57.630 --> 05:00.090
I'M AFRAID SO.

05:00.258 --> 05:01.216
IS ADAM HERE?

05:01.384 --> 05:03.677
OH, YES. HE'S IN
THE SUPPLY ROOM.

05:03.845 --> 05:04.803
THANK YOU.

05:04.971 --> 05:07.097
WE'LL LET YOU GET BACK
TO YOUR WORK.

05:07.265 --> 05:08.765
I WON'T BE A MINUTE.

05:11.644 --> 05:12.436
ADAM...

05:12.603 --> 05:13.437
MRS. INGALLS.

05:13.604 --> 05:14.730
YOU KNOW, UM...

05:14.897 --> 05:16.148
[WHISPERING]
Monday is Mary's
birthday.

05:16.316 --> 05:17.607
YES.

05:17.775 --> 05:20.110
WELL, WE'RE PLANNING
A LITTLE SURPRISE
PARTY FOR HER.

05:20.278 --> 05:21.570
OH, SHE'LL LOVE IT.

05:21.738 --> 05:23.113
IT'LL HAVE TO BE
AFTER 7:00.

05:23.281 --> 05:25.574
IT TAKES ME THAT LONG
TO FINISH WITH
THE SUPPER SITTING.

05:25.742 --> 05:28.118
THAT WAY, WE CAN
HAVE THE DINING ROOM
ALL TO OURSELVES.

05:28.286 --> 05:29.536
I'LL KEEP THE SECRET.

05:29.704 --> 05:32.289
I'LL JUST TELL MARY I WANT
TO STOP BY FOR A VISIT.

05:32.457 --> 05:34.541
FINE. SEE YOU
IN CHURCH TOMORROW.

05:34.709 --> 05:35.792
OK.

05:42.008 --> 05:44.134
WHAT A SHAME.
NO SCHOOL.

05:44.302 --> 05:46.261
NOT FUNNY,
ANDREW.

05:46.429 --> 05:47.721
NO, MA'AM.

05:47.889 --> 05:49.097
WELL, WE'LL JUST HAVE
TO TEACH AT HOME.

05:49.265 --> 05:50.682
WE'VE BOTH
DONE IT BEFORE.

05:50.850 --> 05:53.477
WELL, WHAT BOTHERS
ME IS THE REST OF
THE CHILDREN IN TOWN.

05:53.644 --> 05:54.978
THERE MUST BE SOME
POOR FOLKS WHO'D LIKE

05:55.146 --> 05:57.147
TO HAVE THEIR CHILDREN
GET AN EDUCATION--

05:57.315 --> 05:59.608
PARENTS WHO CAN'T READ
AND WRITE THEMSELVES.

05:59.776 --> 06:02.152
WELL, APPARENTLY
THE TOWN COUNCIL
DOESN'T CARE.

06:02.320 --> 06:03.904
WELL, WE DO.

06:04.072 --> 06:06.156
THERE MUST BE
SOMETHING WE CAN DO.

06:06.324 --> 06:08.367
WE'RE BOTH TEACHERS.

06:08.534 --> 06:10.160
ALL WE NEED IS
A SCHOOLROOM.

06:10.328 --> 06:13.205
WELL, YOU HAVE
MORE THAN ENOUGH TO
HANDLE AT THE HOTEL.

06:14.540 --> 06:15.957
I'LL TAKE CARE
OF THE TEACHING.

06:16.125 --> 06:18.752
I DON'T DO ANYTHING
IN THAT ROOM
ALL DAY ANYWAY.

06:18.920 --> 06:21.296
ALL WE HAVE TO DO IS
FIND A SCHOOLROOM.

06:21.464 --> 06:23.298
WHEN I'M FINISHED
WITH THE NOON MEAL,
WE CAN CHECK AROUND.

06:23.466 --> 06:26.510
WELL, I'LL START RIGHT
AWAY, AND I'LL MEET YOU
BACK AT THE HOTEL.

06:26.677 --> 06:27.803
-OK.
-OK!

06:27.970 --> 06:28.845
COME ON, ANDREW.

06:29.013 --> 06:30.097
GOOD LUCK.

06:47.073 --> 06:48.031
THERE YOU ARE.

06:48.199 --> 06:52.035
MA'AM, WE'RE
READY TO ORDER.

06:52.203 --> 06:55.080
THIS IS THE PRETTY LADY
I TOLD YOU ABOUT,
MR. STANDISH.

06:56.082 --> 06:57.707
MY PLEASURE, MA'AM.

06:57.875 --> 06:59.918
WHAT DO YOU HAVE
YOU THINK I MIGHT LIKE?

07:01.045 --> 07:02.462
YOU HAVE
YOUR MENU.

07:02.630 --> 07:04.756
I KNOW, BUT WE'RE
GOING TO BE EATING
IN HERE A LOT AND--

07:04.924 --> 07:06.383
Charles: I'LL
TAKE THIS ORDER.

07:06.551 --> 07:07.717
THE LADY WILL TAKE
THE ORDER, INGALLS.

07:07.885 --> 07:09.469
THAT'S HER JOB.

07:10.888 --> 07:12.180
I NOTICED THE WINDOWS
OUT FRONT.

07:12.348 --> 07:14.266
WHEN WAS THE LAST TIME
YOU WASHED THEM?

07:16.227 --> 07:17.477
THIS MORNING.

07:17.645 --> 07:19.771
Standish: WELL, I WANT
YOU TO WASH THEM AGAIN.

07:19.939 --> 07:22.399
DON'T BE IN SUCH
A HURRY NEXT TIME.

07:22.567 --> 07:23.567
[LAUGHS]

07:23.734 --> 07:24.901
Man: WHY YOU
STANDING THERE?

07:25.069 --> 07:26.278
YOU WORK FOR
MR. STANDISH.

07:26.446 --> 07:27.821
HE GAVE YOU AN ORDER.

07:29.574 --> 07:30.907
CHARLES, PLEASE.

07:39.917 --> 07:41.918
[PIANO PLAYING]

07:43.254 --> 07:45.714
JONATHAN WAS AWFULLY
QUIET AT SUPPER TONIGHT.

07:47.592 --> 07:49.718
HE'S WORRIED
HE HASN'T GOTTEN
A JOB YET.

07:49.886 --> 07:53.346
HE WILL. IT'S ONLY
BEEN A FEW DAYS.

07:58.936 --> 08:00.937
YOU WERE PRETTY
QUIET YOURSELF.

08:03.441 --> 08:04.733
I SUPPOSE.

08:08.571 --> 08:10.155
BECAUSE OF
STANDISH TODAY?

08:17.038 --> 08:17.954
WE NEED THE MONEY.

08:18.122 --> 08:19.372
AM I SUPPOSED
TO LIKE IT,

08:19.540 --> 08:21.374
BEING HUMILIATED
IN FRONT OF MY WIFE?

08:23.544 --> 08:25.003
HOW'S A MAN
SUPPOSED TO GET

08:25.171 --> 08:27.506
ANY THINKING DONE
WITH THAT NOISE GOING ON?

08:30.426 --> 08:32.761
IT COULD BE WORSE.

08:32.929 --> 08:35.555
THE OLESONS
HAVE TO SLEEP IN
THE SAME BUILDING.

08:58.996 --> 09:01.498
WE HAD SOME
GOOD NEWS TODAY.

09:01.666 --> 09:03.208
ALICE GOT
THE STABLE LIVERY OWNER

09:03.376 --> 09:05.627
TO GIVE US PART
OF THE BARN
FOR A SCHOOLROOM.

09:05.795 --> 09:08.129
SHE'LL MAKE
THE ANNOUNCEMENT
IN CHURCH TOMORROW.

09:08.297 --> 09:09.422
THAT'S
REALLY GREAT NEWS.

09:09.590 --> 09:12.842
MY CHILDREN
WILL GO TO SCHOOL
IN A STABLE.

09:13.010 --> 09:14.427
THAT'S REALLY
GOOD NEWS.

09:22.979 --> 09:24.604
CHARLES INGALLS...

09:27.316 --> 09:28.775
LOOK AT ME.

09:34.574 --> 09:38.243
PEOPLE WHO TAKE
ADVANTAGE OF OTHERS
JUST DEMEAN THEMSELVES.

09:40.329 --> 09:42.539
THEY DESERVE OUR PITY,

09:42.707 --> 09:44.040
NOT OUR ANGER.

09:46.127 --> 09:47.544
AND THERE'S
ANOTHER THING...

09:49.547 --> 09:51.131
LOOK AT ME.

09:54.093 --> 09:58.096
YOU WERE THE ONE
WHO SAID YOU COULD BE
HAPPY IN THE CITY

09:58.264 --> 10:00.056
IF WE WERE
ALL TOGETHER.

10:02.018 --> 10:03.852
WELL?

10:04.020 --> 10:05.520
WE'RE ALL TOGETHER.

10:16.407 --> 10:18.158
[PEOPLE CHEERING]

10:18.326 --> 10:20.827
WELL, IF WE'RE GOING
TO HAVE ALL THIS
FREE ENTERTAINMENT,

10:20.995 --> 10:24.414
THEN I THINK
WE SHOULD JUST TAKE
ADVANTAGE OF IT.

10:26.125 --> 10:28.001
MAY I HAVE
THE PLEASURE?

10:28.169 --> 10:29.878
YOU CERTAINLY MAY.

11:34.568 --> 11:36.736
HEY! DON'T TOUCH THAT!

11:40.741 --> 11:42.492
PA, COME QUICK!

11:42.660 --> 11:43.785
PA, HURRY!

11:43.953 --> 11:45.161
GET OFF ME!

11:45.329 --> 11:46.830
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA!
ALL RIGHT,
ALL RIGHT!

11:46.997 --> 11:48.748
THAT'S ENOUGH.
THAT'S ENOUGH.

11:48.916 --> 11:49.833
GIVE ME
THOSE PAPERS.

11:50.000 --> 11:51.626
HE'S GOT
SOME MONEY, TOO.

11:51.794 --> 11:53.461
ALL RIGHT.
LET ME HAVE IT.

11:53.629 --> 11:54.713
COME ON.

11:56.924 --> 11:58.174
GOT YOURSELF
A LITTLE BIT
OF TROUBLE,

11:58.342 --> 11:59.426
DIDN'T YOU, SON?

11:59.593 --> 12:00.844
I DIDN'T DO ANYTHING.

12:01.011 --> 12:02.512
YOU DIDN'T DO ANYTHING?

12:02.680 --> 12:05.140
SUPPOSE YOU EXPLAIN
TO ME HOW YOU GOT MY
NEWSPAPERS AND MY MONEY.

12:05.307 --> 12:08.727
WELL, I WAS JUST
BUYING A NEWSPAPER.

12:08.894 --> 12:11.020
I WAS COUNTING
THE MONEY

12:11.188 --> 12:14.691
TO SEE IF YOU HAD CHANGE
FOR A 50-CENT PIECE
THAT MY PA GAVE ME,

12:14.859 --> 12:19.696
AND, WELL, THAT'S WHEN
WHAT'S-HER-FACE YELLED,
AND IT SCARED ME.

12:19.864 --> 12:20.947
I SEE.

12:21.115 --> 12:22.699
WELL, SUPPOSE YOU SHOW
WHAT'S-HER-FACE AND ME

12:22.867 --> 12:25.201
THAT 50-CENT PIECE
YOU WANTED TO
MAKE CHANGE FOR.

12:25.369 --> 12:29.956
YEAH...UM...
IT'S RIGHT...

12:30.124 --> 12:31.207
OH, NO.

12:31.375 --> 12:32.584
Charles:
WHAT'S THE MATTER?

12:34.253 --> 12:36.463
I MUST HAVE
DROPPED IT.

12:36.630 --> 12:40.675
OH, MY PA'S GOING
TO SKIN ME ALIVE.

12:40.843 --> 12:43.720
HE GIVE ME
THAT 50-CENT PIECE
TO GET HIM A PAPER.

12:43.888 --> 12:45.221
IT WAS JUST
AN ACCIDENT, WASN'T IT?

12:45.389 --> 12:47.474
OH, HE DON'T CARE.

12:47.641 --> 12:49.684
HE'S GOING
TO WHIP ME GOOD.

12:49.852 --> 12:51.019
Charles: WELL,
I'LL TELL YOU WHAT.

12:51.187 --> 12:52.228
I HATE TO SEE A FELLOW
GET A WHIPPING

12:52.396 --> 12:53.563
FOR JUST HAVING
AN ACCIDENT LIKE THAT.

12:53.731 --> 12:55.231
WHY DON'T I JUST
GO ALONG WITH YOU,

12:55.399 --> 12:56.608
AND WE'LL TALK
TO YOUR PA ABOUT IT
AND EXPLAIN IT TO HIM?

12:56.776 --> 13:00.820
UH...NO, NO.
NO NEED FOR THAT.

13:00.988 --> 13:02.405
WOULDN'T DO NO GOOD.

13:02.573 --> 13:03.740
I DON'T MIND.
WORTH A TRY. COME ON.

13:03.908 --> 13:06.326
UH, BUT YOU CAN'T.

13:06.494 --> 13:08.244
UH...YOU HAD THE MEASLES?

13:08.412 --> 13:10.288
THE MEASLES?

13:10.456 --> 13:11.706
UH-HUH.

13:11.874 --> 13:13.124
NO, NO, I HAVEN'T
HAD THE MEASLES.

13:13.292 --> 13:14.626
NOW, WHAT DOES THAT
HAVE TO DO WITH IT?

13:15.920 --> 13:17.378
I WAS AFRAID
OF THAT.

13:18.631 --> 13:21.466
MY PA'S GOT THEM
REAL BAD.

13:21.634 --> 13:24.594
HE'S, UH...
WHATCHAMACALLIT.

13:24.762 --> 13:26.554
UH...QUA-QUA--

13:26.722 --> 13:27.931
-QUARANTINED?
-QUARANTINED, YEAH.

13:28.098 --> 13:29.474
QUARANTINED.
OH, THAT'S A SHAME.

13:29.642 --> 13:30.892
YEAH.

13:31.060 --> 13:32.936
JUST HAVE TO FACE
UP TO IT ALONE.

13:33.103 --> 13:34.562
I'LL SEE YOU.

13:34.730 --> 13:37.774
UH...I DON'T WANT YOU
TO HAVE ANY MORE
ACCIDENTS AROUND HERE.

13:37.942 --> 13:39.609
YOU GET MY MEANING?

13:39.777 --> 13:41.319
YES, SIR.

13:43.781 --> 13:45.114
ALL RIGHT, GO ON.

13:49.787 --> 13:53.414
DID YOU EVER
HEAR ANYONE MAKE UP
AN EXCUSE LIKE THAT?

13:53.582 --> 13:56.251
MM-HMM, YEAH...YOU.

13:56.418 --> 13:58.336
I GOT TO WASH
THE WINDOWS.

14:00.965 --> 14:03.424
[RINGING]

14:19.692 --> 14:22.151
Harriet: MY BIRDS
SEEM MORE DAINTY.

14:24.488 --> 14:26.865
Caroline:
OH, UM...MRS. OLESON.

14:27.032 --> 14:28.283
YES?

14:28.450 --> 14:31.035
WILL NELLIE AND WILLIE
BE STARTING TOMORROW?

14:31.203 --> 14:32.328
STARTING WHAT?

14:32.496 --> 14:35.164
SCHOOL. ALICE MADE
THE ANNOUNCEMENT...

14:35.332 --> 14:37.292
OH, HO HO HO!
MRS. INGALLS,

14:37.459 --> 14:39.544
I HAVE NO INTENTION
OF LETTING MY CHILDREN

14:39.712 --> 14:41.129
GO TO SCHOOL
IN A BARN. HA HA HA!

14:41.297 --> 14:42.630
WELL, HARRIET,
THE CHILDREN
NEED EDUCATION.

14:42.798 --> 14:43.756
IT MAY NOT
BE IDEAL--

14:43.924 --> 14:46.050
THEY ARE GOING TO
GO TO SCHOOL, NELS--

14:46.218 --> 14:47.760
THE WINOKA SCHOOL.

14:47.928 --> 14:49.012
THE WHAT?

14:49.179 --> 14:52.265
YOU HEARD ME.
THANK YOU ANYWAY,
MRS. INGALLS.

14:53.642 --> 14:55.143
EXCUSE ME.

14:58.898 --> 15:00.523
DO YOU REALIZE HOW
EXPENSIVE IT WOULD BE

15:00.691 --> 15:02.442
TO ENROLL THESE CHILDREN
IN A PRIVATE SCHOOL?

15:02.610 --> 15:03.693
OF COURSE I DO.

15:03.861 --> 15:05.361
WELL, THEN YOU REALIZE
WE CAN'T AFFORD IT.

15:05.529 --> 15:08.197
NELS, NOT IN FRONT
OF THE CHILDREN.

15:08.365 --> 15:11.284
WHAT DIFFERENCE DOES
IT MAKE WHERE I SAY IT?
IT'S THE TRUTH.

15:11.452 --> 15:13.328
NELLIE AND WILLIE,
WE'LL SEE YOU
IN THE ROOM.

15:13.495 --> 15:14.954
YOU DON'T HAVE TO
ARGUE ABOUT SCHOOL.

15:15.122 --> 15:16.873
-WE DON'T HAVE TO
GO TO ONE.
-HEE HEE!

15:17.041 --> 15:18.082
TO THE ROOM!

15:18.250 --> 15:19.876
YES, MA'AM.

15:20.044 --> 15:23.212
HOW DARE YOU MAKE
THOSE CHILDREN THINK
THAT WE'RE POOR!

15:23.380 --> 15:25.381
HARRIET, WE'RE NOT
GOING TO STARVE,

15:25.549 --> 15:26.758
BUT WE'RE NOT RICH.

15:26.926 --> 15:28.885
WELL, THE CHILDREN
ARE USED
TO BEING RICH.

15:29.053 --> 15:30.929
WELL, THEY'RE GOING TO
HAVE TO GET USED TO
BEING NOT SO RICH.

15:31.096 --> 15:33.556
WELL, IF YOU LOVED THEM,
YOU WOULD SEND THEM
TO THE SCHOOL.

15:33.724 --> 15:35.725
WELL, I'VE GOT
A LIFE INSURANCE POLICY.

15:35.893 --> 15:37.560
IF I KILLED MYSELF, THEN
YOU'D HAVE ENOUGH MONEY

15:37.728 --> 15:39.103
TO ENROLL THEM
IN THE PRIVATE SCHOOL.

15:39.271 --> 15:40.355
NELS!

15:41.607 --> 15:43.983
WOULD YOU DO THAT FOR US?

15:47.905 --> 15:49.405
OF COURSE NOT!

15:49.573 --> 15:51.366
OH, I SHOULD HAVE KNOWN!

15:51.533 --> 15:54.077
FOR ONE MOMENT THERE,
I FELT SO CLOSE TO YOU!

15:54.244 --> 15:55.411
NOW, YOU LISTEN TO ME.

15:55.579 --> 15:57.246
I'M DOING
THE BEST I CAN.

15:57.414 --> 15:59.082
IF YOU WANT TO SEND THEM
TO A PRIVATE SCHOOL,

15:59.249 --> 16:00.750
THEN YOU PAY FOR IT.

16:00.918 --> 16:02.377
OH, HOW?

16:02.544 --> 16:03.920
GET A JOB.

16:04.088 --> 16:07.090
ALL RIGHT, I WILL!

16:07.257 --> 16:08.758
[MOCKING]
GET A JOB!

16:15.349 --> 16:18.601
ALL RIGHT, I WILL.

16:18.769 --> 16:21.354
YOU WILL NOT!

16:21.522 --> 16:23.147
I WILL!

16:23.315 --> 16:26.109
YOU'RE THE ONE WHO
WANTED ME TO TAKE A JOB
IN THE FIRST PLACE.

16:26.276 --> 16:27.944
A DECENT JOB
IN A DECENT PLACE.

16:28.112 --> 16:30.196
WELL, YOU WORK HERE.

16:30.364 --> 16:31.447
I HAVE TO.

16:31.615 --> 16:32.782
WELL, SO DO I,

16:32.950 --> 16:36.494
AND WILL YOU
STOP YELLING IN FRONT
OF THE CHILDREN!

16:36.662 --> 16:38.621
OH, WHAT'S THE USE?

16:38.789 --> 16:40.873
IMPOSSIBLE MAN!

16:41.041 --> 16:43.334
MOTHER, MAYBE
FATHER'S RIGHT.

16:43.502 --> 16:45.086
I MEAN, YOU SAID HOW
EMBARRASSING IT MUST BE

16:45.254 --> 16:48.256
FOR MRS. INGALLS
BEING A WAITRESS.

16:49.675 --> 16:52.468
I'M NOT A WAITRESS!

16:52.636 --> 16:55.054
HEAVENS.
WAITRESSES SERVE FOOD.

16:55.222 --> 16:57.557
YEAH. MA JUST
SERVES WHISKEY.

16:57.725 --> 16:58.766
Harriet: YES.

16:58.934 --> 16:59.976
WELL, REVEREND ALDEN
ALWAYS SAID

17:00.144 --> 17:01.561
WHISKEY WAS
THE DRINK OF THE DEVIL.

17:01.729 --> 17:04.981
OH, NELLIE,
THAT'S NONSENSE.

17:05.149 --> 17:09.819
EVEN DR. BAKER
PRESCRIBED ALCOHOL FOR
SOME OF HIS PATIENTS.

17:09.987 --> 17:12.822
THERE SURE IS
A LOT OF SICK PEOPLE
DOWNSTAIRS.

17:14.700 --> 17:15.742
I HAVE TO GO
TO WORK NOW,

17:15.909 --> 17:19.495
AND I WANT THE LIGHTS
OUT AT 9:00--SHARP!

17:19.663 --> 17:21.289
-YES, MOTHER.
-YES'M.

17:22.541 --> 17:23.833
I GUESS WE'RE GOING
TO HAVE TO TELL

17:24.001 --> 17:26.669
THE KIDS AT SCHOOL
THAT MA'S A NURSE.

17:28.505 --> 17:31.132
[PIANO MUSIC STARTS]

17:43.604 --> 17:45.438
OK, LADY, GO TO WORK.

17:52.988 --> 17:53.988
SIX MORE, FRED.

17:54.156 --> 17:55.573
-THEY'RE COMING UP.
-OK.

17:55.741 --> 17:56.699
-JOSIE?
-YEAH?

17:56.867 --> 17:59.285
THIS IS HARRIET.
SHOW HER
WHAT TO DO.

17:59.453 --> 18:01.120
YOU BET.

18:01.288 --> 18:03.706
YOU JUST WATCH ME FOR
A FEW MINUTES, SWEETIE,

18:03.874 --> 18:05.917
AND YOU'LL CATCH ON
RIGHT AWAY.

18:07.669 --> 18:10.713
UH, YOU SEE, MOST OF
THE MONEY IS MADE FROM TIPS.

18:10.881 --> 18:11.798
OH...

18:11.965 --> 18:15.968
SO, THE BETTER YOU LOOK,
THE MORE THE TIPS.

18:16.136 --> 18:19.138
IF YOU DON'T MIND
MY SAYING SO,

18:19.306 --> 18:20.556
YOU COULD SURE USE
A LITTLE MAKEUP

18:20.724 --> 18:22.850
ON THOSE CROW'S-FEET
OF YOURS.

18:24.770 --> 18:27.188
I BEG YOUR PARDON.
HEH HEH.

18:27.356 --> 18:29.148
THESE ARE NOT
CROW'S-FEET.

18:29.316 --> 18:30.525
REALLY?

18:30.692 --> 18:32.276
YES, REALLY.

18:32.444 --> 18:33.736
THEY'RE LAUGH LINES.

18:33.904 --> 18:37.323
HONEY, NOTHING'S
THAT FUNNY.

18:40.786 --> 18:43.162
[ROULETTE WHEEL CLICKING]

18:50.587 --> 18:51.754
EVERYBODY ASLEEP?

18:51.922 --> 18:54.674
LAURA'S WORKING
ON A SURPRISE FOR MARY.

18:54.842 --> 18:56.926
IT'S A BRAILLE CARD.

18:57.094 --> 18:59.095
BRAILLE. HOW IN THE WORLD
DID SHE LEARN TO DO THAT?

18:59.263 --> 19:00.972
ADAM LOANED HER A BOOK.

19:01.140 --> 19:03.766
I'LL BE DARNED.
THAT'S GOOD.

19:03.934 --> 19:06.394
WE GOT TO GET MARY
A PRESENT TOMORROW.

19:07.604 --> 19:10.106
I'VE GOT ABOUT
A DOLLAR SAVED IN TIPS.

19:10.274 --> 19:12.775
YOU'RE NOT GOING
TO GET MUCH IN
THE CITY FOR A DOLLAR.

19:12.943 --> 19:14.235
[SIGHS]

19:14.403 --> 19:16.821
I COULD ASK STANDISH
FOR AN ADVANCE.

19:16.989 --> 19:18.698
DON'T IF YOU DON'T
WANT TO.

19:19.783 --> 19:21.617
YOU WORRIED
ABOUT MY PRIDE?

19:21.785 --> 19:25.955
NO. YOUR PRIDE
IS REAL, NOT FALSE.

19:26.123 --> 19:27.623
WELL, WE'RE DOING
A GOOD JOB HERE.

19:27.791 --> 19:29.458
HE OUGHT TO GIVE US
AN ADVANCE.

19:29.626 --> 19:30.877
I'LL ASK HIM
IN THE MORNING.

19:31.044 --> 19:32.545
YOU SHOP FOR
THE NOON MEAL.

19:32.713 --> 19:34.046
I WONDER
WHAT SHE NEEDS.

19:34.214 --> 19:35.840
AW, YOU'RE STARTING
TO SOUND LIKE ME.

19:36.008 --> 19:38.509
THE HECK WITH WHAT
SHE NEEDS. JUST GET HER
SOMETHING SHE'D LOVE.

19:38.677 --> 19:40.303
ALL RIGHT, I WILL.

19:40.470 --> 19:43.222
I CAN'T WAIT FOR
MY BIRTHDAY. I KNOW
JUST WHAT I WANT.

19:43.390 --> 19:45.683
OH? YOU ALWAYS SAY
YOU NEVER WANT ANYTHING.

19:45.851 --> 19:47.643
WELL, I DO THIS YEAR.

19:47.811 --> 19:49.395
EARMUFFS...

19:49.563 --> 19:52.440
THE BIGGEST PAIR OF
EARMUFFS IN THE WORLD.

19:52.608 --> 19:55.193
[LAUGHTER]

19:56.945 --> 19:58.613
OH...

19:59.656 --> 20:03.618
HA HA HA!
IT'S AWFUL HERE!

20:03.785 --> 20:05.870
HA HA HA!

20:31.521 --> 20:32.438
HEY, NELS.

20:32.606 --> 20:33.856
AH, GOOD MORNING,
CHARLES.

20:34.024 --> 20:35.358
I WISH I COULD SLEEP
IN THE MORNING.

20:35.525 --> 20:36.609
IT'S THE ONLY TIME
THIS PLACE IS QUIET.

20:36.777 --> 20:38.194
OH, I KNOW
WHAT YOU MEAN.

20:38.362 --> 20:40.363
YOU REALLY TAKE THINGS
FOR GRANTED WHEN YOU
LIVE IN THE COUNTRY.

20:40.530 --> 20:42.865
THAT YOU DO. HEY,
LISTEN, WE'RE HAVING
A SURPRISE BIRTHDAY PARTY

20:43.033 --> 20:44.033
FOR MARY TONIGHT
AFTER SUPPER,

20:44.201 --> 20:45.576
AND WE WONDERED
IF YOU COULD JOIN US.

20:45.744 --> 20:47.578
BE KIND OF NICE
HAVING ALL THE OLD
NEIGHBORS TOGETHER.

20:47.746 --> 20:49.121
WE WOULDN'T MISS THAT
FOR THE WORLD.

20:49.289 --> 20:50.665
-GREAT. WE'LL COUNT
ON SEEING YOU THERE.
-RIGHT.

20:50.832 --> 20:52.458
-IS STANDISH UP
IN THE OFFICE?
-NO, NO.

20:52.626 --> 20:55.336
HE'S BACK
BEHIND THE BAR
COUNTING THE LIQUOR.

20:55.504 --> 20:56.629
OK. THANKS A LOT.
SEE YOU TONIGHT.

20:56.797 --> 20:57.880
RIGHT.

21:01.802 --> 21:04.011
MR. STANDISH.

21:04.179 --> 21:05.888
INGALLS, WHAT IS IT?

21:06.056 --> 21:07.848
I KNOW I'M SUPPOSED TO BE
PAID EVERY OTHER WEEK,

21:08.016 --> 21:10.059
BUT TODAY IS MY DAUGHTER'S
16th BIRTHDAY, AND--

21:10.227 --> 21:11.477
YOU'RE SUPPOSED TO BE
PAID EVERY OTHER WEEK,

21:11.645 --> 21:12.979
AND THAT'S WHEN
YOU'LL BE PAID.

21:14.898 --> 21:17.900
WELL, WE'VE ALREADY WORKED
A WEEK, AND I'M NOT
ASKING FOR A FULL WAGE.

21:18.068 --> 21:19.151
I JUST WANT ENOUGH
MONEY TO BE ABLE TO BUY--

21:19.319 --> 21:21.737
I'VE ALREADY
ANSWERED YOU.

21:21.905 --> 21:23.739
NOW, LET ME FINISH
WHAT I'M DOING.

21:43.760 --> 21:46.304
-HI, ALBERT.
-HELLO.

21:46.471 --> 21:49.432
YOUR PA GIVE YOU
A WHIPPING, OR WAS
HE TOO SICK?

21:49.599 --> 21:51.058
YOU'LL NEVER KNOW.

21:51.226 --> 21:54.770
I'M JUST KIDDING.
I LOOKED FOR YOU
IN CHURCH YESTERDAY.

21:54.938 --> 21:56.689
I DON'T GO TO CHURCH.

21:56.857 --> 21:58.899
YOU BELIEVE IN GOD,
DON'T YOU?

21:59.943 --> 22:02.486
HE NEVER DID
NOTHING FOR ME.

22:02.654 --> 22:05.031
MAYBE YOU WEREN'T
DESERVING.

22:05.198 --> 22:06.615
I'M TRYING TO WORK.

22:06.783 --> 22:08.868
YEAH. HE'S
TRYING TO WORK.

22:10.287 --> 22:13.122
YOU WANT TO PLAY PUSH
AND SHOVE, YOU PICKED
THE WRONG PERSON.

22:19.796 --> 22:21.255
IT'S A GOOD THING
YOU'RE A GIRL.

22:21.423 --> 22:24.508
DON'T LET THAT
STOP YOU.

22:24.676 --> 22:27.011
WELL, I GOT MY
SCHOOL CLOTHES ON.

22:27.179 --> 22:28.846
ME, TOO.

22:35.937 --> 22:37.438
HERE'S
YOUR PENNY.

22:41.651 --> 22:43.694
I'LL SEE YOU
LATER!

22:43.862 --> 22:45.571
I'LL BE HERE!

22:47.491 --> 22:48.657
HE'S A PAIN.

22:48.825 --> 22:51.535
YEAH. HIS PA'S
MR. STANDISH.

22:51.703 --> 22:53.329
HE OWNS THE TOWN.

22:54.373 --> 22:56.540
HEY, WE'RE STARTING
SCHOOL TODAY.

22:56.708 --> 22:58.876
THAT'S WHY I WAS
LOOKING FOR YOU
IN CHURCH YESTERDAY.

22:59.044 --> 23:00.503
YEAH, I HEARD
ABOUT IT.

23:00.670 --> 23:02.171
AREN'T YOU GOING?

23:02.339 --> 23:03.714
NOPE.

23:03.882 --> 23:05.508
I DON'T NEED SCHOOL.

23:05.675 --> 23:07.927
BESIDES,
I GOT TO WORK.

23:08.095 --> 23:09.428
YOU REAL POOR?

23:09.596 --> 23:12.890
NO. I MAKE OUT
JUST FINE.

23:14.601 --> 23:17.436
JUST DON'T NEED
SCHOOL, THAT'S ALL.

23:17.604 --> 23:20.022
MY FOLKS THINK SCHOOL
IS AWFUL IMPORTANT.

23:20.941 --> 23:23.984
HMM. MY FOLKS DON'T.

23:27.364 --> 23:28.656
HELLO, LAURA.

23:28.824 --> 23:30.991
HOW DO YOU
LIKE OUR NEW
UNIFORMS?

23:31.159 --> 23:33.244
WE GOT THEM JUST
THIS MORNING.

23:33.412 --> 23:35.538
WE GO TO THE
WINOKA SCHOOL,
YOU KNOW.

23:35.705 --> 23:37.373
SO? WE GO TO SCHOOL.

23:37.541 --> 23:39.708
I KNOW...
IN A BARN.

23:39.876 --> 23:41.544
DON'T YOU
THINK IT'S KIND
OF FUNNY,

23:41.711 --> 23:44.004
CHILDREN
GOING TO STUDY
IN A STABLE?

23:44.172 --> 23:47.091
NO FUNNIER THAN
A JACKASS GOING TO
STUDY IN A SCHOOL.

23:47.259 --> 23:49.343
HA! THAT'S
A GOOD ONE, LAURA!

23:49.511 --> 23:51.345
WE'LL BE LATE,
WILLIE.

23:56.059 --> 23:57.768
I WISH I WAS GOING
TO SCHOOL WITH YOU.

23:57.936 --> 23:59.937
I HATE WEARING THIS TIE!

24:00.105 --> 24:01.188
WILLIE!

24:01.356 --> 24:03.107
I'M COMING!

24:04.234 --> 24:06.777
WELL, I GOT TO GO.

24:06.945 --> 24:09.238
ARE YOU SURE YOU
WON'T CHANGE YOUR MIND
ABOUT SCHOOL?

24:09.406 --> 24:14.827
NOPE. BESIDES,
ME AND MY PA ARE GOING
TO GO FISHING TODAY.

24:14.995 --> 24:15.744
I LOVE FISHING.

24:15.912 --> 24:17.329
IF YOU EVER GO
ON A SATURDAY,

24:17.497 --> 24:19.665
I'D SURE LIKE
TO JOIN YOU.

24:19.833 --> 24:21.083
MAYBE.

24:21.251 --> 24:24.420
MY PA AND ME,
WE LIKE TO FISH ALONE.

24:24.588 --> 24:27.131
OH. WELL, SEE YOU.

24:28.717 --> 24:29.800
YEAH.

24:38.477 --> 24:40.686
ARE YOU A HUNGRY GIRL?

24:40.854 --> 24:42.480
YOU'LL EAT SOON.

24:46.985 --> 24:50.779
CHARLES, I KNOW JUST
WHAT WE CAN GET MARY
FOR HER BIRTHDAY.

24:50.947 --> 24:52.781
A MRS. CARROLL
CAME IN THIS MORNING,

24:52.949 --> 24:54.783
AND SHE WAS
WEARING A HAT.

24:54.951 --> 24:58.954
WELL, CHARLES, IT WAS
JUST ABOUT THE LOVELIEST
THING I EVER SAW.

24:59.122 --> 25:00.289
I ASKED HER
WHERE SHE GOT IT,

25:00.457 --> 25:03.876
AND IT TURNS OUT
SHE HAS A STORE IN TOWN.

25:04.044 --> 25:05.461
HER HATS ARE EXPENSIVE,

25:05.629 --> 25:08.964
BUT SHE WAS SO NICE,
SHE SAID SHE'D GIVE ME
A DISCOUNT.

25:09.132 --> 25:10.508
ISN'T THAT WONDERFUL?

25:11.635 --> 25:12.635
THAT'S WONDERFUL.

25:12.802 --> 25:14.637
DID YOU SEE
MR. STANDISH YET?

25:16.556 --> 25:20.142
NO, I DIDN'T HAVE
A CHANCE TO SEE HIM
YET THIS MORNING.

25:20.310 --> 25:23.812
WELL, THE HAT WILL COST
ABOUT $4.00 OR $5.00.

25:23.980 --> 25:25.648
I KNOW IT'S HIGH,

25:25.815 --> 25:27.691
BUT THEY DO SELL
FOR MUCH MORE.

25:27.859 --> 25:30.152
WELL, THAT'S NO PROBLEM.
I'LL GET THE MONEY FROM HIM.

25:30.320 --> 25:31.612
THERE'S NO HURRY.

25:31.780 --> 25:34.156
I'M JUST GOING
TO FINISH UP HERE
AND FEED THE BABY.

25:34.324 --> 25:35.824
SHE'S BEEN
SO GOOD TODAY.

25:35.992 --> 25:38.827
YOU KNOW, SHE DOESN'T
MIND THE NOISE IN
THE KITCHEN ONE BIT.

25:38.995 --> 25:40.204
THAT'S GOOD.

25:40.372 --> 25:42.915
WELL, LOOK, I'LL GET OVER
THERE AND GET THE MONEY.

25:47.504 --> 25:50.673
GRACE,
YOUR SISTER'S GOING
TO BE SO SURPRISED.

25:50.840 --> 25:52.174
[CAROLINE CHUCKLES]

25:52.342 --> 25:55.010
DON'T GET MUCH CALL
FOR FIDDLES IN THE CITY.

25:55.178 --> 25:56.637
IT'S A COUNTRY ITEM.

25:56.805 --> 25:59.098
I KNOW, BUT THAT'S
A FINE VIOLIN.

25:59.266 --> 26:01.350
DON'T TELL ME
MY BUSINESS, YOUNG MAN.

26:01.518 --> 26:03.769
I'VE HAD PAWNSHOPS
FOR 40 YEARS.

26:05.230 --> 26:07.147
$3.00.

26:07.315 --> 26:09.108
$8.00.

26:09.276 --> 26:10.484
$4.00.

26:10.652 --> 26:11.569
$7.00.

26:11.736 --> 26:14.572
$5.00 OUTRIGHT SALE.
TAKE IT OR LEAVE IT.

26:17.993 --> 26:19.076
ALL RIGHT.
I'LL TAKE IT.

26:19.244 --> 26:21.495
GOOD. I'LL GET YOU
YOUR MONEY.

26:32.340 --> 26:34.675
HEY, YOU!

26:34.843 --> 26:36.385
I'LL GET HIM.

27:36.279 --> 27:37.821
ALL RIGHT, SON.
LET'S GO.

27:39.032 --> 27:40.616
COME ON. I WENT
EASY WITH YOU
THE FIRST TIME.

27:40.784 --> 27:42.242
THIS TIME, I CAN'T.

27:42.410 --> 27:43.702
COME ON OUT.

27:45.121 --> 27:46.705
WE'RE GOING TO
GO TELL YOUR FATHER.

27:49.125 --> 27:50.459
GIVE ME ONE MORE CHANCE.

27:50.627 --> 27:52.252
UH-UH. NO MORE
CHANCES. NOW, IT'S
FOR YOUR OWN GOOD.

27:52.420 --> 27:53.671
THE SOONER WE GET
TO YOUR PLACE,

27:53.838 --> 27:56.298
THE SOONER
YOU'RE GOING TO
GET IT OVER WITH.

27:56.466 --> 27:59.677
[PANTING]

27:59.844 --> 28:01.553
THIS IS MY PLACE.

28:03.056 --> 28:05.641
WHAT?

28:05.809 --> 28:07.685
THIS IS WHERE I LIVE.

28:09.312 --> 28:11.230
WHAT, DID YOU
RUN AWAY FROM HOME?

28:11.398 --> 28:12.147
NOPE.

28:12.315 --> 28:13.649
WHAT'S YOUR NAME?

28:13.817 --> 28:14.817
ALBERT.

28:14.984 --> 28:15.818
ALBERT WHAT?

28:15.985 --> 28:19.571
JUST ALBERT.
I'M A BASTARD.

28:19.739 --> 28:21.782
HEY, NOW, WHAT KIND
OF TALK IS THAT?

28:23.076 --> 28:25.703
UH, THAT'S WHEN THEY DON'T
KNOW WHO YOUR PA IS.

28:25.870 --> 28:28.330
I KNOW WHAT THE WORD
MEANS. I DON'T LIKE IT.

28:28.498 --> 28:30.124
ME NEITHER.

28:31.334 --> 28:35.796
THAT WAS WHAT THEY CALLED
ME BACK AT THE HOME--

28:35.964 --> 28:38.382
THAT AND A WHOLE BUNCH
OF OTHER THINGS.

28:39.801 --> 28:41.510
THAT'S WHY I RAN AWAY.

28:43.638 --> 28:45.514
WHEN DID YOU RUN AWAY?

28:45.682 --> 28:48.517
OH...

28:48.685 --> 28:51.061
ABOUT 3 YEARS NOW.

28:51.229 --> 28:54.690
3 YEARS? YOU'VE BEEN
LIVING IN THIS PLACE
FOR 3 YEARS?

28:54.858 --> 28:59.194
OH, SOMETIMES HERE,
SOMETIMES OTHER PLACES.

28:59.362 --> 29:00.821
I DO ALL RIGHT.

29:02.574 --> 29:05.117
I WORK A LITTLE BIT,
SHINING SHOES.

29:06.202 --> 29:07.327
I MAKE MY WAY.

29:07.495 --> 29:09.496
IF YOU MAKE YOUR WAY,
THEN WHY DO YOU STEAL?

29:09.664 --> 29:12.207
I NEEDED A LIGHT.

29:12.375 --> 29:14.626
I'VE BEEN
USING CANDLES, SEE?

29:14.794 --> 29:17.880
BUT THEY'RE NOT
BRIGHT ENOUGH TO READ.

29:18.047 --> 29:19.548
I LIKE READING.

29:22.761 --> 29:24.678
WHERE'S THIS PLACE
YOU RAN AWAY FROM?

29:27.682 --> 29:29.767
CAN'T TELL YOU.

29:29.934 --> 29:31.143
WHY NOT?

29:31.311 --> 29:32.895
BECAUSE YOU'LL
SEND ME BACK,

29:33.062 --> 29:35.856
AND I AIN'T GOING BACK.

29:36.024 --> 29:37.858
WELL, I COULD TAKE
YOU TO THE SHERIFF.
YOU KNOW THAT?

29:38.026 --> 29:40.736
THERE'S A LAW
AGAINST STEALING.

29:40.904 --> 29:43.489
ANYTHING'S BETTER
THAN GOING BACK.

29:45.408 --> 29:47.826
YOU DO WHAT
YOU THINK IS RIGHT.

29:54.709 --> 29:57.169
ALL RIGHT, COME ON.
GIVE ME THE LAMP.
I'LL TAKE IT BACK.

30:10.767 --> 30:12.351
COULDN'T YOU JUST SAY
YOU DIDN'T FIND ME

30:12.519 --> 30:13.602
AND THEN I COULD
KEEP THE LAMP?

30:13.770 --> 30:14.853
NO.

30:16.397 --> 30:17.481
ALL RIGHT.

30:23.446 --> 30:24.655
HEY, MISTER?

30:27.826 --> 30:30.285
THANKS FOR NOT SENDING
ME TO THE SHERIFF.

30:54.143 --> 30:55.936
GOT IT. HERE YOU GO.

30:56.104 --> 30:57.354
YOU CAUGHT HIM.

30:57.522 --> 30:59.022
NO. NO, I DIDN'T CATCH HIM,
BUT I GOT THE LAMP BACK.

30:59.190 --> 31:00.315
MUCH OBLIGED.

31:00.483 --> 31:03.193
LITTLE THIEF OUGHT
TO GET A THRASHING.

31:03.361 --> 31:04.319
HERE'S YOUR $5.00.

31:04.487 --> 31:05.696
THANK YOU.

31:06.739 --> 31:08.282
SAY, HOW MUCH IS
THAT LAMP?

31:08.449 --> 31:09.825
A DOLLAR.

31:12.745 --> 31:14.538
I'LL TAKE IT. THANKS.

31:22.422 --> 31:24.548
Charles: THERE YOU GO.
YOU NEED A LAMP
TO READ BY.

31:27.010 --> 31:29.845
WE'RE HAVING
A BIRTHDAY PARTY
TONIGHT AT THE HOTEL.

31:30.013 --> 31:33.891
YOU WANT SOME CAKE
AND MILK, YOU'RE WELCOME
TO JOIN US...

31:34.058 --> 31:35.559
ABOUT 7:00.

31:53.494 --> 31:57.289
HERE YOU GO. HE'D
ONLY ADVANCE ME $4.00.

31:57.457 --> 31:59.041
OH, THAT'S FINE.

31:59.208 --> 32:00.375
I MADE SOME MORE
IN TIPS THIS MORNING.

32:00.543 --> 32:01.418
OH, GOOD.

32:01.586 --> 32:03.045
DID HE MIND GIVING YOU
THE ADVANCE?

32:03.212 --> 32:05.172
NO, NO, NOT AT ALL.
IT WAS FINE.

32:05.340 --> 32:07.132
MAYBE HE'S NOT
SO BAD AFTER ALL.

32:07.300 --> 32:09.051
YOU KNOW, THERE'S GOOD
IN EVERYONE.

32:10.678 --> 32:12.387
I SUPPOSE.

32:12.555 --> 32:13.847
I PUT THE BABY DOWN
FOR A NAP.

32:14.015 --> 32:15.098
I WON'T BE LONG.

32:15.266 --> 32:16.642
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

32:24.651 --> 32:26.193
GOOD IN EVERYONE!

32:33.326 --> 32:37.412
JONATHAN.
FIND ANYTHING?

32:37.580 --> 32:39.790
NO. A COUPLE OF GUYS
LOOKING FOR SALESMEN,

32:39.958 --> 32:42.459
BUT I GUESS
I JUST AIN'T THE TYPE.

32:42.627 --> 32:43.877
YOU'LL FIND SOMETHING.

32:44.045 --> 32:45.921
I SURE HOPE SO.

32:46.089 --> 32:47.297
WILL WE SEE YOU
AT THE PARTY TONIGHT?

32:47.465 --> 32:49.883
OH, YEAH. I WOULDN'T
MISS IT FOR ANYTHING.

32:50.051 --> 32:51.760
GUESS I BETTER
GET GOING.

32:51.928 --> 32:52.761
GOOD LUCK.

32:52.929 --> 32:54.012
THANK YOU.

33:20.456 --> 33:23.166
[MUSIC PLAYING ON SOUNDTRACK]

33:26.129 --> 33:27.587
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

33:27.755 --> 33:28.839
COME IN.

33:30.466 --> 33:31.383
YOU ALL READY?

33:31.551 --> 33:33.301
JUST PUTTING ON
MY SHOES.

33:33.469 --> 33:36.138
HEY, WHEN WE SEE
MY FOLKS TONIGHT,

33:36.305 --> 33:37.681
DON'T SAY ANYTHING
ABOUT MY BIRTHDAY,

33:37.849 --> 33:39.433
JUST IN CASE
THEY FORGOT. I MEAN,

33:39.600 --> 33:41.018
WHAT WITH JUST GETTING
SETTLED IN AND ALL,

33:41.185 --> 33:42.728
THEY JUST MAY HAVE.

33:42.895 --> 33:44.104
YOU'RE PROBABLY RIGHT.

33:44.272 --> 33:45.647
THEY DIDN'T SAY
ANYTHING TO ME.

33:45.815 --> 33:47.315
I'M READY.

33:47.483 --> 33:49.067
SEE IF MY TIE'S
STRAIGHT.

33:56.409 --> 33:57.492
PERFECT.

34:02.790 --> 34:04.875
YOU LOOK BEAUTIFUL.

34:07.378 --> 34:09.379
THANK YOU, SIR.

34:09.547 --> 34:11.465
16 YEARS OLD, HUH?

34:12.675 --> 34:15.469
YOU'D BEST BE GETTING
MARRIED SOON, YOUNG LADY,

34:15.636 --> 34:17.929
OR THEY'LL BE CALLING
YOU A SPINSTER.

34:19.182 --> 34:22.726
MAYBE SOME HANDSOME
GENTLEMAN WILL ASK ME.

34:22.894 --> 34:25.479
WELL, I'M SURE
HE WILL...

34:25.646 --> 34:27.314
ONCE HE GETS
HIS NERVE UP.

34:45.541 --> 34:46.958
LET'S GO,
BIRTHDAY GIRL.

34:54.550 --> 34:57.302
Charles: COME ON.
EVERYBODY IN HERE.

34:57.470 --> 34:58.762
OH, MY!

35:04.060 --> 35:05.894
ALL RIGHT.
NOW, EVERYBODY'S GOING
TO STAY IN HERE.

35:06.062 --> 35:08.063
DON'T MAKE A SOUND
TILL I GET THEM SEATED.

35:08.231 --> 35:10.524
THEN OUT WITH
A BIG "SURPRISE"
AND A "HAPPY BIRTHDAY."

35:10.691 --> 35:11.733
I'LL WAIT FOR THEM
IN THE LOBBY.

35:11.901 --> 35:13.485
OK.

35:13.653 --> 35:14.528
Mrs. Oleson: OH, MY.

35:14.695 --> 35:16.947
WHAT A FUNNY
LITTLE CAKE.

35:17.115 --> 35:17.948
HARRIET...

35:18.116 --> 35:20.951
HUH? OH! WELL,
WHAT I MEANT WAS,

35:21.119 --> 35:23.286
WHAT A...
QUAINT LITTLE CAKE.

35:23.454 --> 35:25.163
HARRIET,
BE QUIET.

35:26.415 --> 35:28.333
Caroline: I KNOW
IT'S HARD FOR YOU,
MRS. OLESON,

35:28.501 --> 35:30.585
BUT YOU WON'T HAVE
TO BE QUIET FOR LONG.

35:30.753 --> 35:32.170
[LAUGHING]

35:40.221 --> 35:44.808
HEY, GLOVER, LOOK WHAT
THAT BLIND SCHOOLTEACHER'S
GOT WITH HIM.

35:52.441 --> 35:53.608
COME ON.

36:02.076 --> 36:03.410
EXCUSE ME, FRIEND.

36:03.578 --> 36:05.203
DIDN'T SEE YOU COMING.

36:05.371 --> 36:06.538
YOU PROBABLY
DON'T KNOW IT, BOY,

36:06.706 --> 36:08.290
BUT THAT'S A GOOD-LOOKING
WOMAN THERE.

36:08.457 --> 36:11.251
IF YOU'LL EXCUSE US,
WE'RE LATE.

36:11.419 --> 36:13.461
JUST WANTED TO
INTRODUCE MYSELF IS ALL.

36:13.629 --> 36:16.089
MY NAME'S HARLAN,
MA'AM.

36:21.971 --> 36:23.680
HEY, GLOVER,

36:23.848 --> 36:25.807
SHE'S BLIND, TOO.

36:25.975 --> 36:28.393
EVEN A GUY AS UGLY AS YOU
GOT A CHANCE WITH HER.

36:28.561 --> 36:29.311
HA HA HA!

36:29.478 --> 36:30.437
WILL YOU PLEASE LET US GO?

36:30.605 --> 36:32.522
JUST TRYING TO BE
A GOOD NEIGHBOR.

36:32.690 --> 36:34.941
JUST TRYING TO HELP
THE YOUNG LADY GET
WHERE SHE'S GOING.

36:35.109 --> 36:36.234
Charles: HARLAN!

36:47.830 --> 36:50.373
ADAM, I WANT YOU
AND MARY TO GO IN
THE HOTEL, ALL RIGHT?

36:58.466 --> 37:00.050
I'LL BE IN IN A MINUTE.

37:01.719 --> 37:03.094
PA, YOU COME
WITH US.

37:05.389 --> 37:07.182
I'LL BE IN IN A MINUTE.
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

37:07.350 --> 37:08.475
COME ON, MARY.

37:21.656 --> 37:23.448
THAT'S A FINE-LOOKING
LITTLE BLIND GIRL

37:23.616 --> 37:26.201
YOU GOT THERE,
INGALLS...

37:26.369 --> 37:27.577
FINE-LOOKING.

37:37.880 --> 37:39.381
[WHISPERING]
OK, everybody.

37:39.548 --> 37:41.424
Here they come.
Shh! Now, be quiet.

37:41.592 --> 37:43.093
Mary:
MA! MA!

37:43.261 --> 37:47.222
MARY, MARY? WHAT'S
WRONG? WHAT IS IT?

37:47.390 --> 37:48.890
PA...PA'S
OUTSIDE WITH
SOME MEN.

37:49.058 --> 37:51.393
I ASKED HIM
TO COME IN,
BUT HE WOULDN'T.

37:51.560 --> 37:52.686
MA, I'M AFRAID.

37:52.853 --> 37:55.397
NELS, COME ON.
THE REST OF YOU
STAY HERE.

38:02.446 --> 38:03.530
NELS!

38:10.705 --> 38:13.331
LORD HAVE
MERCY, CHARLES.
WHAT HIT YOU?

38:15.001 --> 38:17.794
IT WAS...HARLAN.

38:18.754 --> 38:20.630
IS THAT THE GUY
FROM THE SALOON?

38:22.466 --> 38:24.092
YEAH.

38:24.260 --> 38:25.552
CLEAN HIM UP.

38:29.682 --> 38:30.765
CHARLES.

38:49.869 --> 38:52.537
I THINK YOU TWO
JUST BEAT UP ON
A FRIEND OF MINE.

38:56.876 --> 38:58.001
THAT'S RIGHT.

38:59.837 --> 39:03.006
WHY DON'T
YOU MOVE ALONG BEFORE
YOU HAVE TROUBLE, TOO?

39:03.174 --> 39:04.924
YOU'RE THE BOUNCER
HERE, AIN'T YOU?

39:05.968 --> 39:07.761
WHY DON'T YOU
GET TO BOUNCING?

39:33.329 --> 39:35.580
[JONATHAN GROANING]

39:41.003 --> 39:42.170
YOU AIN'T
GONNA BOTHER

39:42.338 --> 39:44.714
MY FRIEND AND
HIS FAMILY ANYMORE,
ARE YOU?

39:44.882 --> 39:46.716
NO.

39:46.884 --> 39:50.553
THAT'S GOOD.
I KNOW YOU'RE
A MAN OF YOUR WORD.

39:54.350 --> 39:56.434
-HEY, YOU THERE.
-NOW, LOOK, YOU'RE
A FRIEND OF HIS...

39:56.602 --> 39:57.727
DON'T TRY
AND BE NO HERO.

39:57.895 --> 39:59.979
TAKE IT EASY. TAKE IT
EASY. YOU LIVE HERE?

40:00.147 --> 40:01.398
YEAH.

40:01.565 --> 40:02.607
GOT A JOB?

40:02.775 --> 40:03.900
NO.

40:04.068 --> 40:06.403
WANT TO MAKE
$40 A MONTH?

40:06.570 --> 40:09.322
REPLACE HARLAN.
START TOMORROW.

40:12.368 --> 40:13.493
ALL RIGHT.

40:13.661 --> 40:15.036
QUEENS OVER 10s.

40:28.259 --> 40:29.843
ARE YOU ALL
RIGHT, CHARLES?

40:31.137 --> 40:33.263
YEAH. I FEEL GREAT.

40:33.431 --> 40:35.390
WHAT HAPPENED
IN THERE, ANYWAY?

40:35.558 --> 40:37.308
WELL, NOTHING.

40:37.476 --> 40:39.394
I THINK
I GOT ME A JOB.

40:39.562 --> 40:40.478
YOU WHAT?

40:40.646 --> 40:41.855
UH...I'LL TELL
YOU LATER.

40:42.022 --> 40:44.274
WE GOT A PARTY
TO GO TO.
CAN YOU WALK?

40:44.442 --> 40:46.025
YOU BET I CAN WALK.
JUST GIVE ME A HAND.

40:46.193 --> 40:47.402
COME ON.

40:47.570 --> 40:49.696
Caroline: THIS FROSTING
SMELLS WONDERFUL.

40:49.864 --> 40:52.907
SOMETHING'S WRONG.
WHY AREN'T THEY BACK?

40:53.075 --> 40:55.952
WELL, THERE'S
NOTHING WRONG.

40:56.120 --> 40:57.871
NOW, JONATHAN TOLD US
TO WAIT INSIDE,

40:58.038 --> 41:00.039
AND THAT'S WHAT
WE'RE GOING TO DO.

41:00.207 --> 41:00.999
[DOOR OPENS]

41:01.167 --> 41:03.877
THERE. YOU SEE?
IT MUST BE THEM.

41:05.963 --> 41:07.005
IS EVERYTHING ALL RIGHT?

41:07.173 --> 41:08.673
EVERYTHING IS FINE.

41:08.841 --> 41:10.300
OH!

41:10.468 --> 41:12.093
SHH! I'M SORRY
I'M LATE.

41:13.596 --> 41:15.263
COME ON. SIT DOWN.

41:15.431 --> 41:16.431
ALL RIGHT.

41:16.599 --> 41:19.142
Mary: PA, I WAS SO
AFRAID YOU'D GOTTEN

41:19.310 --> 41:21.352
INTO A FIGHT
WITH THOSE TWO MEN.

41:21.520 --> 41:22.562
YOU DON'T HAVE
TO WORRY ABOUT ME.

41:22.730 --> 41:24.772
I'M A FARMER,
NOT A FIGHTER.

41:24.940 --> 41:26.649
Jonathan: YOU CAN
SAY THAT AGAIN.

41:29.320 --> 41:31.613
MARY WANTS TO OPEN
HER PRESENTS.

41:31.780 --> 41:33.448
LET'S GET TO OPENING.

41:39.788 --> 41:41.372
I HAVE TO
BE HONEST. I...

41:43.542 --> 41:45.376
I KNOW WHAT'S
IN THE PACKAGE.

41:46.879 --> 41:48.588
MA AND I TALKED
IT OVER, AND...

41:51.091 --> 41:53.176
WELL, I...

41:53.344 --> 41:55.178
I HOPE YOU
UNDERSTAND, PA.

42:14.365 --> 42:16.241
I KNOW WHAT YOU
WERE TRYING TO DO.

42:18.494 --> 42:21.246
BUT THE GREATEST
PRESENT YOU COULD
GIVE ME...

42:22.498 --> 42:24.499
IS TO BE ABLE
TO HEAR YOU PLAY
THIS FIDDLE

42:24.667 --> 42:26.000
ON MY BIRTHDAY.

42:28.462 --> 42:30.088
IT ALWAYS HAS BEEN.

42:34.468 --> 42:36.094
I LOVE YOU, PA.

42:45.020 --> 42:48.022
LAURA,
PASS IT TO PA.

43:14.091 --> 43:15.717
I LOVE YOU, TOO,
DARLING.

43:21.181 --> 43:25.393
UH...LET'S--LET'S
LIGHT THE CANDLES.

43:25.561 --> 43:26.853
[DOOR CLOSES]

43:44.288 --> 43:47.290
Laura: THERE.
THEY'RE ALL LIT.

43:47.458 --> 43:49.751
HEY, HOLD IT
ONE SECOND, NOW.

43:49.918 --> 43:51.502
DON'T MAKE THAT WISH YET.

43:53.088 --> 43:55.048
COME ON IN.
YOU JOIN US, BOY.

43:56.884 --> 43:58.301
COME ON.

44:00.638 --> 44:02.555
THERE YOU GO.
HAVE A SEAT RIGHT HERE.

44:02.723 --> 44:05.266
EVERYBODY, I'D LIKE YOU
TO MEET A FRIEND OF MINE.
HIS NAME IS ALBERT.

44:05.434 --> 44:06.768
All: HI, ALBERT.

44:06.935 --> 44:08.645
I SPENT A LITTLE TIME
AT ALBERT'S PLACE TODAY.

44:08.812 --> 44:10.480
I THOUGHT I'D RETURN
THE FAVOR TO HIM.

44:10.648 --> 44:12.023
Caroline: YOU'RE
JUST IN TIME, ALBERT.

44:12.191 --> 44:14.275
MARY'S GOING
TO MAKE A WISH.

44:14.443 --> 44:17.320
Laura: OH! I ALMOST
FORGOT MY CARD.

44:23.160 --> 44:24.035
IT'S IN BRAILLE.

44:24.203 --> 44:25.244
Laura: UH-HUH.

44:25.412 --> 44:28.247
ADAM LOANED ME A BOOK
AND A BRAILLE WRITER.

44:33.253 --> 44:34.504
"DEAR MARY...

44:36.465 --> 44:38.800
"YOU KNOW I'M
NOT GOOD AT WORDS

44:38.967 --> 44:41.177
THE WAY
YOU ARE, BUT..."

44:49.311 --> 44:53.189
[CRYING]
"I JUST WANTED
YOU TO KNOW

44:53.357 --> 44:54.774
HOW MUCH I LOVE YOU."

44:59.154 --> 45:01.322
"I DON'T THINK
I EVER TOLD YOU THAT."

45:05.452 --> 45:10.164
"I GUESS KIDS JUST DON'T
SAY IT TO EACH OTHER."

45:13.335 --> 45:18.172
"WELL, YOU'RE 16 NOW..."

45:19.508 --> 45:21.175
"SO YOU'RE NOT
A KID ANYMORE..."

45:22.636 --> 45:24.303
"SO I CAN SAY IT."

45:29.435 --> 45:31.894
"YOU'RE THE BEST SISTER
IN THE WHOLE WORLD."

45:34.857 --> 45:36.482
"LOVE, LAURA."

45:39.695 --> 45:41.237
[CRYING]

45:41.405 --> 45:43.197
I LOVE YOU.

45:51.415 --> 45:53.082
HEY, YOU TWO DON'T STOP THAT
HUGGING AND KISSING,

45:53.250 --> 45:55.501
YOU'RE GOING TO
HAVE NOTHING BUT WAX
FOR ICING ON THAT CAKE.

45:55.669 --> 45:56.502
NOW, MAKE YOUR WISH.

45:56.670 --> 45:59.297
[CRYING AND LAUGHING]

46:03.093 --> 46:04.427
I LOVE YOU.

46:16.064 --> 46:19.233
I DON'T...I DON'T HAVE
ANYTHING TO WISH FOR.

46:23.238 --> 46:26.115
I HAVE EVERYTHING
IN THE WORLD

46:26.283 --> 46:28.034
RIGHT HERE IN THIS ROOM.

46:32.122 --> 46:33.748
GOD BLESS YOU ALL.

46:39.880 --> 46:40.838
[BLOWS]

46:41.006 --> 46:43.716
WHEN CAN WE CUT
THE CAKE? I'M HUNGRY!

46:43.884 --> 46:46.177
[SOBBING]
OH, WILLIE!

46:46.345 --> 46:47.845
[CAROLINE LAUGHS]

46:55.771 --> 46:58.064
[CLAPPING]
